Task Description:

Create a simple script file and push it to repo.
Create a project in Jenkins connected to your GitHub repository. 
When a commit is made to your repo, automatically build must get triggered from Jenkins and
the output must be shared to me via email.

====================================================================================================================================
Steps:

1. Create and Launch an EC2 instance.
Name: jenkins-task-2
AMI: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, t3.medium

2. Install java, jenkins packages & Verfiy jenkins service is up and running in browser & terminal.

java :
sudo apt update
sudo apt install fontconfig openjdk-21-jre
java -version

jenkins:
sudo wget -O /etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc]" \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install jenkins

commands:
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl status jenkins

2.Initialize git Created a simple-script.sh & readme file.
3.created SSH key token and pushed the commited file  to git repo
4. Created the jenkinsfile pipeline script

----------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.1,2 ;2.5 -----------

5. In Google Acct , Created amn App Password for jenkinstas-2 and updated the system settings for 
    Email notification & Extended Email Notification.
      SMTP Server - smtp.gmail.om
      Default user email suffix - @gmail.com
      Username - email id 
      Password - Google Acct's newly created app password
      Enabled SMTP Authentication & Opted for TLS
      SMTP Port - 587 
      Tested Configuration & successfully sent test email to Gmail.

----------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.3 -----------

6. Launch Jenkins and setup login credentials , plugins.

Performed below action uner manage jenkins
  Plugins  - installed git, pipeline stage view, Extension email notification , Mailer plugin.

7. Github repo added webhook 
      payload URL -  http://<public-ip>:8080/github-webhook/ ; 
      choosing content type as - application/json under repo settings.
      Enabled Just a Push Event & saved.

----------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.4 -----------

8.  Create Jenkins Pipeline Project 
  Name - jenkins-task2-pipeline
  description : creating a pipeline to trigger every time a commit is made to github repo
    Pipeline To automate build and push email.
    1.Getting the simplescript.sh from github
    2.Running the script 

9. Pipeline Configuration 
      Trigger - Enabled webhook by checking out Github trigger for GITScm Polling 
      Pipeline Script from SCM 
            Choose SCM - Git 
            Updated Repo URL - https://github.com/anithaambrose/jenkins-t2-repo.git
            Branch - */main
            Mentioned Script Path - Jenkinsfile
      click apply & save.

10. In the terminal add , commit and pushed the jenkinsfile as second commit to github to trigger the pipeline.

----------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.6 -----------

11. verifed automation proces: since the commit of jenkins file triggered the pipeline, 
Also made changes to git repo - readme file and verified the pipeline auto trigger and notified through email on success.

----------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.7 -----------



